Hazelnut Pesto
  --Sur la Table

2 cloves garlic, peeled
3/4 c hazelnuts, toasted, roughly chopped
1 c flat-leaf parsley, washed and dried, stems removed
1/4 c mint, washed and dried, stems removed
1/2 c evoo
1/4 c Parmesan cheese, grated
2 tbsp sherry vinegar, plus more to taste

In the bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade, add garlic, hazelnuts, parsley and sage. Process by pulsing until the mixture resembles a rough chop, ~1 min. Add olive oil in a steady steam and process to a smooth paste. Transfer the mixture to a large mixing bowl and use a silicone spatula to mix in Parmesan cheese and vinegar, stirring until well combined. Taste and season with salt, pepper and more vinegar as needed.
